\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 By defining, building, and running a Docker image, we\'92ve started to familiarize ourselves with some of the terms we will use in the project; for example, image and container.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We will use the same Jupyter notebook we just created to analyze our dataset and train the model.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 We will create another Dockerfile to run the web service using a similar approach in a later milestone.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \
